annotationA: Ribosomal protein S3A is an essential component of the small ribosomal subunit that functions in protein synthesis. It is classified as a 'Minute' gene as heterozygous mutants exhibit a slower developmental rate and small adult bristles
annotationB: 60S ribosomal protein L15; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: translation; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL15 family
